billion a year in spend.

01:08:16.994 --> 01:08:18.410
Before you get to
the whole world,

01:08:18.410 --> 01:08:20.260
if you're just focused
on African Americans,

01:08:20.260 --> 01:08:24.250
like our total spend
is $1.2 trillion.

01:08:24.250 --> 01:08:27.819
So shifting how that's
spent in even small ways

01:08:27.819 --> 01:08:30.279
could have enormous
impacts on demand.

01:08:30.279 --> 01:08:31.810
Now, take it a different way.

01:08:31.810 --> 01:08:35.170
That $1.2 trillion is
generating about 24 million jobs

01:08:35.170 --> 01:08:37.250
across the US economy.

01:08:37.250 --> 01:08:41.029
Very, very few of those are
within our own communities,

01:08:41.029 --> 01:08:41.569
right?

01:08:41.569 --> 01:08:44.510
I think it's
important that we do

01:08:44.510 --> 01:08:49.479
what we expect other people to
do because we get to control

01:08:49.479 --> 01:08:50.890
how we spend and when we spend.

01:08:50.890 --> 01:08:52.930
Nobody else gets to do that.

01:08:52.930 --> 01:08:56.550
And I want people
to say, listen, man,

01:08:56.550 --> 01:08:58.550
I, too, am interested
in economic development

01:08:58.550 --> 01:08:59.770
because I kind of get it.

01:08:59.770 --> 01:09:00.811
You know what I'm saying?

01:09:00.811 --> 01:09:03.474
Nothing gets better when
there's economic deprivation.

01:09:03.474 --> 01:09:04.640
So I want to march with you.

01:09:04.640 --> 01:09:05.939
I love it, march.

01:09:05.939 --> 01:09:08.410
